.el .ds Aq '
.TH git-worktree-merge 1  "git-worktree-merge 1.10.0" 
.SH NAME
git\-worktree\-merge \- Merge branches across worktrees
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBgit\-worktree\-merge\fR [\fB\-\-into\fR] [\fB\-\-abort\fR] [\fB\-\-continue\fR] [\fB\-\-quit\fR] [\fB\-m \fR] [\fB\-F\fR|\fB\-\-file\fR] [\fB\-\-edit\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-edit\fR] [\fB\-\-cleanup\fR] [\fB\-\-ff\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-ff\fR] [\fB\-\-ff\-only\fR] [\fB\-\-squash\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-squash\fR] [\fB\-\-commit\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-commit\fR] [\fB\-\-signoff\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-signoff\fR] [\fB\-s\fR|\fB\-\-strategy\fR] [\fB\-X\fR|\fB\-\-strategy\-option\fR] [\fB\-S\fR|\fB\-\-gpg\-sign\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-gpg\-sign\fR] [\fB\-\-verify\-signatures\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-verify\-signatures\fR] [\fB\-\-allow\-unrelated\-histories\fR] [\fB\-\-stat\fR] [\fB\-n\fR|\fB\-\-no\-stat\fR] [\fB\-\-adopt\-target\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-adopt\-target\fR] [\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR] [\fB\-r\fR|\fB\-\-remove\fR] [\fB\-b\fR|\fB\-\-and\-branch\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] [\fISOURCE_OR_TARGET\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Merges one or more source branches into a target worktree\*(Aqs branch.
.PP
When \-\-into is omitted, the target is the current worktree\*(Aqs branch,
mirroring `git merge`. When \-\-into <target> is supplied, the merge is
performed against that worktree\*(Aqs branch from wherever you are.
.PP
Multiple sources invoke git\*(Aqs octopus strategy, announced explicitly.
.PP
Finish commands (\-\-abort, \-\-continue, \-\-quit) take an optional positional
<worktree|branch>; default to the current worktree\*(Aqs branch.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-into\fR \fI<TARGET>\fR
Target worktree/branch. Defaults to the current worktree\*(Aqs branch
.TP
\fB\-\-abort\fR
Abort an in\-progress merge in the named worktree (defaults to CWD)
.TP
\fB\-\-continue\fR
Continue an in\-progress merge in the named worktree (defaults to CWD).

When continuing a squash\-staged state, the commit\-message flags (`\-\-no\-edit`, `\-m`, `\-F`, `\-\-signoff`, `\-\-gpg\-sign`, `\-\-cleanup`) may be supplied to control the commit step. They are forwarded to `git commit` and are *not* treated as start\-mode flags.
.TP
\fB\-\-quit\fR
Quit an in\-progress merge without resetting the index (defaults to CWD)
.TP
\fB\-m\fR \fI<MSG>\fR
Commit message for the merge commit (mirrors `git merge \-m`)
.TP
\fB\-F\fR, \fB\-\-file\fR \fI<FILE>\fR
Read the commit message from FILE (mirrors `git merge \-F`)
.TP
\fB\-\-edit\fR
Launch the editor to edit the merge commit message
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-edit\fR
Accept the auto\-generated merge commit message without editing
.TP
\fB\-\-cleanup\fR \fI<MODE>\fR
Message cleanup mode (mirrors `git merge \-\-cleanup`)
.TP
\fB\-\-ff\fR
Allow fast\-forward merges (git\*(Aqs default behavior)
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-ff\fR
Always create a merge commit, even when fast\-forward is possible
.TP
\fB\-\-ff\-only\fR
Refuse to merge if fast\-forward is not possible
.TP
\fB\-\-squash\fR
Squash the source\*(Aqs changes into a single staged diff, without creating a merge commit
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-squash\fR
Explicitly disable squash (cancel a config default of `merge.squash`)
.TP
\fB\-\-commit\fR
Automatically create the merge commit after a successful merge
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-commit\fR
Leave the merge staged without committing
.TP
\fB\-\-signoff\fR
Add a Signed\-off\-by trailer to the merge commit
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-signoff\fR
Explicitly disable signoff (cancel a config default)
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-strategy\fR \fI<STRAT>\fR
Merge strategy to use (e.g. `ours`, `recursive`, `octopus`)
.TP
\fB\-X\fR, \fB\-\-strategy\-option\fR \fI<OPT>\fR
Strategy\-specific option (repeatable; mirrors `git merge \-X`)
.TP
\fB\-S\fR, \fB\-\-gpg\-sign\fR [\fI<KEYID>\fR]
GPG\-sign the merge commit. Accepts an optional KEYID; omit to use the default key
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-gpg\-sign\fR
Do not GPG\-sign the merge commit (cancels `commit.gpgsign` config)
.TP
\fB\-\-verify\-signatures\fR
Verify that the tip commit of the source is signed with a valid key
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-verify\-signatures\fR
Do not verify signatures on the source tip commit
.TP
\fB\-\-allow\-unrelated\-histories\fR
Allow merging histories that share no common ancestor
.TP
\fB\-\-stat\fR
Show a diffstat at the end of the merge
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-no\-stat\fR
Suppress the diffstat at the end of the merge
.TP
\fB\-\-adopt\-target\fR
When the target has no worktree and the merge is not a pure fast\-forward, create an ephemeral worktree to perform the merge without prompting
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-adopt\-target\fR
When the target has no worktree and the merge is not a pure fast\-forward, refuse without prompting
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-yes\fR
Auto\-accept interactive prompts. Implies \-\-adopt\-target when neither \-\-adopt\-target nor \-\-no\-adopt\-target is supplied. Future\-proofs any new prompts we add
.TP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-remove\fR
Remove the source worktree after a successful merge
.TP
\fB\-b\fR, \fB\-\-and\-branch\fR
Also delete the source branch (requires \-\-remove). Uses `git branch \-d` semantics; refuses to delete if the branch is not fully merged
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Be verbose; show detailed progress
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.TP
[\fISOURCE_OR_TARGET\fR]
Source branches/commits to merge (start mode), OR optional target worktree/branch for \-\-abort / \-\-continue / \-\-quit (finish mode; max one positional)
.SH VERSION
v1.10.0
